<hl>
<seg id=1> China Will Continue Her Opening Policy in Finance </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, January 16 (by Journalist Xu Xintang and Xian Yuhong) - Dai Xianglong, the president of the People's Bank of China, said that China would continue the implementation of opening policy in finance. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In today's press conference for Chinese and foreign journalists, Dai Xianglong stressed that China will not give up the implementation of opening policy in finance because of the financial chaos happened in some Southeast Asia countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said, a group of additional foreign banks and insurance companies opened their affiliated agencies in China last year. By the end of this year, more than 170 foreign-funded financial business agencies were set up in China. </seg>
<seg id=5> In the future, China will properly increase the affiliated agencies of foreign banks and insurance companies in the country; meanwhile, China is preparing to expand foreign bank's trial operation of Renminbi business. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He also emphasized that more cautious management will be performed on the conditions for foreign financial institution to apply their business in China, qualification of senior personnel, and the legitimacy of their business. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He said, because there is no timetable at all for convertible Renminbi under capital account, the issue of postponement of this procedure due to financial crises in Southeast Asia does not exist. </seg>
<seg id=8> However, as for the opening of capital account, we will learn the lessons of financial crises in Southeast Asia and take a more cautious attitude. </seg>
</p>
